html: Just computed someone working 40 hrs a week on Min Wage has annual wage up from £11,200 in 2010 to £17,100 next April. That's +38%. But *post tax* income up 44% due to personal allowance increases. Inflation over this period c. 25%. Those on lowest wages see big real increase
